==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plebification
<hw>Pleb`i*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>plebs</ets> the common people + <ets>-ficare</ets> (in comp.) to
make. See <er>-fy</er>.]</ety> <def>A rendering plebeian; the act of
vulgarizing.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You begin with the attempt to popularize learning . . . but you
will end in the <qex>plebification</qex> of knowledge.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plebiscitary</ent>⟦br⟧
